oc:kn_088366f3 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always — before any output is finalized" ;
    oc:directiveContent "This skill assists with SOX compliance workflows but does not provide audit or legal advice. All testing workpapers and assessments must be reviewed by qualified financial professionals before use in audit documentation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "SOX testing workpapers may be subject to external audit review and regulatory scrutiny; unqualified output could create compliance risk" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_472ab809 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before execution" ;
    oc:directiveContent "User must specify a control area (revenue-recognition, procure-to-pay, payroll, financial-close, treasury, fixed-assets, inventory, itgc, entity-level, journal-entries) and testing period (e.g., 2024-Q4, 2024, 2024-H2)." .

oc:kn_52fb5891 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SideEffect ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always — all output has compliance documentation implications" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Generates structured testing workpapers, sample selections, and deficiency assessments that may become part of formal audit documentation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Output from this skill may be subject to external auditor review and regulatory examination" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_74f628cc a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When executing the full SOX testing workflow" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Identify key controls in the specified area and present control matrix 2. Determine sample size based on frequency and risk 3. Generate sample selection using appropriate method (random/systematic/targeted) 4. Create testing workpaper with test procedures, expected evidence, and results template 5. Provide control-specific test step templates 6. Classify any identified deficiencies (Deficiency / Significant Deficiency / Material Weakness) 7. Deliver complete output package: control matrix, sample selections, workpapers, results templates, deficiency framework, remediation suggestions" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_859647c0 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting samples from a population" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use random selection as the default for transaction-level controls, systematic selection for periodic controls, and targeted selection only as a supplement for risk-based testing." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Different selection methods provide different assurance levels; random selection provides the strongest statistical basis while systematic selection ensures period coverage" .

oc:kn_9f0cf5f9 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:directiveContent """## Control Matrix
| Control # | Description | Type | Frequency | Key/Non-Key | Risk | Assertion |

## Sample Selection
Control: [ID] — [Description]
Period: [Period]
Population: [Count] items, $[Total]
Sample size: [N]
Selection method: [Method]

## Testing Workpaper
Control #: [ID]
Test Objective / Test Procedures / Expected Evidence / Test Results / Exceptions / Conclusion

## Deficiency Assessment
Classification: Deficiency | Significant Deficiency | Material Weakness
Likelihood + Magnitude + Compensating Controls""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Assertion",
        "Control ID",
        "Count",
        "Description",
        "Frequency",
        "Period",
        "Risk",
        "Sample Size",
        "Selection Method",
        "Total",
        "Type" .

oc:kn_d743362d a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating exceptions or control failures" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Deficiency classification follows a three-tier hierarchy: Deficiency → Significant Deficiency → Material Weakness, based on likelihood and magnitude of potential misstatement and existence of compensating controls." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Proper classification drives appropriate remediation urgency and disclosure requirements under SOX 404" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_e4a09a93 a oc:AssumptionBoundary,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before execution begins" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Assumes the user has knowledge of the control environment, population data access, and understands which control area and period to test." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The skill generates templates and frameworks but cannot independently discover the actual control population or transaction data" .

oc:kn_effbe62c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When identifying controls and documenting the control matrix" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Control assertions must map to CEAVOP: Completeness, Existence/Occurrence, Accuracy, Valuation, Obligations/Rights, Presentation/Disclosure." ;
    oc:hasRationale "CEAVOP assertions provide the standard framework linking controls to financial statement risks they mitigate" .

oc:kn_f948e075 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When determining sample size for any control" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Sample sizes must be adjusted upward for higher risk controls, controls with prior-year deficiencies, and controls relied upon by external auditors." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Insufficient sample sizes undermine the statistical validity of testing conclusions and may not satisfy external auditor requirements" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

